   "source": [
    "#Q1.6\n",
    "#Finding the force\n",
    "#defining variables\n",
    "M_moon=7.342e22\n",
    "M_earth=5.9722e24\n",
    "r=385000.6\n",
    "#given in kg, and km, \n",
    "from scipy.constants import G\n",
    "#G is given in m^3 kg^-1 s^-2, convert r to m for ease \n",
    "r *= 1000\n",
    "#squaring the distance r preemptively\n",
    "r **= 2\n",
    "#defining F as the force, calculate F\n",
    "F=(G*((M_moon*M_earth)/r))\n",
    "print(F)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "74c15696-bd39-4d3c-b193-172ef73268e5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Q1.8\n",
    "1. The output is /bin/bash. This shows the value of the SHELL environment variable\n",
    "2. The output of ls is \"Desktop  Documents  Downloads  Music  Pictures  Public  Task1.ipynb  Templates  Videos\". This lists information about the files (by default, the current directory)\n",
    "3. The difference between ls and ls -rtl is that there is more information given with the optional -rtl added, such as the time and date last accessed, the user it belongs to, etc.\n",
    "4. By typing less filename.txt, where filename is replaced by the name of the file you would like to know exists, if it does exist it will show the contents of the file page by page, if not it will return \"No such file or directory\". Alternatively, you can access the file manager application; in this case dolphin, opening it to see if the files exist.\n",
    "5. It copies (the contents of) the file a.txt to a new file b.txt\n",
    "6. It moves (the contents of) the file b.txt to a new file c.txt, and deletes the old file b.txt. In essence, it renames the file.\n",
    "7. It makes a new directory named PROGNUM\n",
    "8. It prints the previously used directory and changes to it, in this case the directory PROGNUM\n",
    "9. Done, using ```mkdir ./Task1```\n",
    "10. It copies a.txt into the Task1 directory. The end dot runs a shell script in the current environment and then returns, rather than running it in a child shell.\n",
    "11. The result is \"a.txt  c.txt  Desktop  Documents  Downloads  Music  Pictures  PROGNUM  Public  Task1.ipynb  Templates  Videos\", showing _all_ directories as the cd command changed from the Task1 directory to the Home directory.\n",
    "12. You can check that it is removed either by accessing the dolphin file manager and checking where it should have been to see if it is there, or using the less a.txt command to see if it returns \"No such file or directory\""
   ]
  },
