   "source": [
    "Q1.15\n",
    "1. Phishing is an attempt to obtain personal and/or private information by mail. It is done usually by attempting to make you open and log into a fake (although often convincing) version of the website you believe is the correct one, or by making you download a file (often .zip) that contains malware of sorts. It can compromise personal information, or even a system, and in doubt of a mail recieved it is always advised to check with others or administrators/IT help of the organisation, such as computergroup@astro.rug.nl. Red flags are a sense of urgency or threat of negative consequences, bad spelling or grammar mistakes, links to suspicious files, websites, URLs, requests for payments, offering of free money or things, unusual email addresses, account detail confirmations, etc. "
   ]
  },
