    "Q1.21 \n",
    "3. From the command ```file```, it is output that it is ASCII text, thus not binary. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "93bd6465-6eef-4e5e-b45c-8b84eab7de51",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Q1.22\n",
    "0. The wildcard * is used as a placeholder for matching one or more occurances for any characters, including 0 characters (not including slash and the first dot of a hidden file) when searching files.\n",
    "1. That command outputs any files whose beginning has any number (or numbers) from 0-9, and that ends with either the c or o letters, however this is only allowed to have one letter in order to be listed.\n",
    "2. The square brackets are used to indicate a list or a range of things (depending on what is written in between them) that is to replace the position it is in. Asterisks (*) indicate any number of those items (one or more) can replace it (in any order), while their absence indicates that it is only to be replaced with 1; files with 2 or more will not be included, e.g. in the list.\n",
    "3. The first command indicates that after the full stop (.), that section is to be replaced with c or o **only** (thus only 1 letter), while the second command indicates that after the full stop it must contain co, no fewer letters and no different order. a command of .* [co] * (without the spaces) would indicate that it can contain any amount of instances of c and/or o, in any order. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "84e0a07a-ba74-44af-bf1c-3c46429a5530",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Q1.23\n",
    "1. After pressing tab, it either completes the file name for you, or if there are still multiple possibilities which it could complete with, then it lists those files beginning with what has been typed.\n",
    "2. Just pressing the arrow keys allows you to automatically type a command you have used before, allowing you to run it again as is or after editing sections of it. Typing ls, or any part of a command before using the arrow keys will skip any that do not contain what you have typed. "
   ]
  },
